  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7096.88 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7115 (-3567.7M) and the massive positive gamma wall at 7100 (+5022.5M), dealers are likely buying this dip aggressively as they're short gamma in this pocket and need to hedge the accelerated move down. The PIN regime with 48.9B in total GEX suggests strong mean reversion forces, but the current positioning in negative gamma territory means dealers are amplifying the move lower until we reclaim 7100. Key inflection points are the 7100 reclaim (where dealer selling pressure kicks in) and any break below the 7100 level which could accelerate down to the GEX flip at 6872.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile action with dealers buying dips until we get back above 7100, then resistance kicks in.",
